about.summary: Python classes for manipulating Lotus Notes/Domino objects via COM

name: noteslib
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "noteslib" %}
{% set version = "2.1.0" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: ca2a4de4a6982785a0160f96085fbc83630fdf0a1f8ed5a9c88a4dd5c3e93ca6

build:
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"
  skip: True  # [unix or py2k]

requirements:
  host:
    - pip ==18.1
    - python
    - pywin32
  run:
    - python
    - pywin32

test:
  imports:
    - noteslib

about:
  home: "https://pypi.org/project/noteslib/"
  license: "MIT"
  license_family: "MIT"
  license_file: "LICENSE"
  summary: "Python classes for manipulating Lotus Notes/Domino objects via COM"
  doc_url: "https://pypi.org/project/noteslib/"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - oblute
    - benhuff
    - mwilson8
